<P>AN APPEAL TO <HI>Honour</HI> and <HI>Ju&s;tice,</HI> Tho' it be of His Wor&s;t ENEMIES.</P>
<P>By DANIEL DE FOE.</P>
<P>BEING A True Account of his Conduct in Publick Affairs.</P>
<Q><BIBL>JEREM. xviii. 18.</BIBL> Come and let us &s;mite him with the
<HI>Tongue,</HI> and let us not give heed to any of his Words.</Q>
<P><HI>LONDON:</HI> Printed for J. BAKER, at the <HI>Black Boy</HI> in <HI>Pater-No&s;ter-Row.</HI> 1715.</P>
